Package org.openliberty.openaz.azapi.constants

The purpose of this package is to provide constants and Enums that can be used by the other packages in the project.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
AzCategoryId AzCategoryId is a marker interface to identify the XACML Category of a collection of AzAttributes (an AzEntity) and to identify individual AzAttributes as being members of a collection of a specific category.
AzDataTypeId This enumeration defines the identifiers for the DataTypes that are used in the XACML specification:
http://docs.oasis-open.org/xacml/2.0/access_control-xacml-2.0-core-spec-os.pdf
See Appendix A.2 ("Data-types") of the XACML 2.0 specification for the source of these DataType definitions and subsequent sections for detail on the semantics of these data types.
AzXacmlStrings This module contains specific XACML-defined identifiers that are used in the course of submitting XACML authorization requests.
 

Enum Summary
AzCategoryIdAction This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML Action Category, AzCategoryIdAction.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_ACTION
AzCategoryIdEnvironment This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML Environment Category, AzCategoryIdEnvironment.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_ENVIRONMENT
AzCategoryIdObligation This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML Obligation Category, AzCategoryIdObligation.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_OBLIGATION
AzCategoryIdResource This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML Resource Category, AzCategoryIdResource.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_RESOURCE
AzCategoryIdStatusDetail This CategoryId indicates that the associated AzEntity or AzAttribute is in the XACML StatusDetail Category, AzCategoryIdStatusDetail.AZ_CATEGORY_ID_STATUSDETAIL
AzCategoryIdSubjectAccess AzCategoryIdSubject* objects correspond to the values defined in XACML 2.0 Appendix B.4
AzCategoryIdSubjectCodebase The AzCategoryIdSubjectCodebase identifier indicates a system entity associated with a local or remote codebase that generated the request.
AzCategoryIdSubjectIntermediary The AzCategoryIdSubjectIntermediary identifier indicates a system entity through which the access request was passed.
AzCategoryIdSubjectRecipient The AzCategoryIdSubjectRecipient identifier indicates the system entity that will receive the results of the request (used when it is distinct from the access-subject).
AzCategoryIdSubjectRequestingMachine The AzCategoryIdSubjectRequestingMachine identifier indicates a system entity associated with the computer that initiated the access request.

Package org.openliberty.openaz.azapi.constants Description

The purpose of this package is to provide constants and Enums that can be used by the other packages in the project. In particular there are enums for XACML Category definitions, for XACML DataType definitions, as well as a variety of other XACML constants. In addition, there are implementation oriented constants for the azapi.pep layer request and response operations.
